      "SummaryText": "Executive Summary for the Erie County Water Authority Sturgeon Point and Van de Water-Water Treatment Plants.   \r\n\r\nAccident Release Prevention Policy: The Authority will take every reasonable action to prevent all accidental releases. This is accomplished by using the most current design, training, and inspecting processes available. The Authority's prevented maintenance program includes\r\n1)\tHaving an analysis of the scrubber media tested twice per year, to verify the scrubber chlorine neutralization capacity.\r\n2)\t The Halogen eclipse automatic shutoff valves are factory tested yearly \r\n3)\t Gas detectors are tested weekly. \r\n4)\tChlorine flexible lines and Header valves from the tank to the manifold are replaced yearly.\r\n\r\nOperating and maintenance procedures are reviewed annually and are officially approved as the accepted operating procedures. \r\nPersonnel are trained on operation and maintenance procedures annually. \r\nThe Stationary Source for Chlorine (CAS No. 7782-50-5) remains the same as the RMP 1999\r\n\r\nSturgeon Point\r\nThe Worst-case Scenario was completed for 2011 the population radius of 3.0 miles is based on a rural area. The Alternative Release Scenario was completed for 2011 the population radius of 1.2 miles is based on a rural area.  \r\n\r\nVan de Water\r\nThe Worst-case Scenario was completed for 2011 the population radius of 1.3 miles is based on an urban area. The Alternative Release Scenario was completed for 2011 the population radius of 0.5 miles is based on an urban area.  \r\nPopulation was based on using the Marplot program. \r\n\r\nAccidental Release Prevention Program remains the same as the RMP 2007\r\n\r\nEmergency Response Program (ERP) revised 'April 2010. The ERP is in the progress of being scheduled and coordinated with the District One Response. \r\n\r\nSturgeon Point\r\nThe contact is the Local Fire Department Fire Chief of the Highland Hose Volunteer Fire Company. \r\n\r\nVan de Water \r\nThe contact is the Local Fire Department Fire Chief of the Brighton Volu"
    },
    {
      "ESSeqNum": 1,
      "FacilityID": 1000027680,
      "SummaryText": "nteer Fire Company.\r\n\r\nPlanned changes to improve Safety, none outstanding.\r\nThe Halogen eclipse yoke assembles were upgrade in 2009, to reduce the potential chlorine release when connecting chlorine cylinders.\r\nEmergency Contact is 11 trained Hazwoper Site Coordinators to assist Hazmat personnel when responding to a release. \r\nIn 2009 personnel are equipped with full face mask which are interchangeable as an escape mask or positive displacement mask."
    }
